# Flutter architecture

App root: `flutter/weight_sovereignty/`. Package imports: `package:weight_sovereignty/...`.

## Layers (top → bottom)

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| presentation | `lib/src/presentation/` | Widgets, screens, theme; minimal logic |
| application | `lib/src/application/` | Use cases, orchestration, Riverpod providers |
| data | `lib/src/data/` | Repository implementations, `local_storage.dart` |
| domain | `lib/src/domain/` | Entities, configs, repo **interfaces** only |

**Dependency rule:** presentation → application → data → domain. Domain never imports Flutter, Riverpod, or data.

## Naming

- `*_repo.dart` in `domain/repo/` — abstract contracts
- `*_repository.dart` in `data/` — Isar-backed implementations
- `*_service.dart` in `application/` — composes repos, triggers recalc, exposes providers
- `entity/` — day-scoped **runtime** records (`DailyLog`, `Food`, `Workout`)
- `config/` — **preset/template** Isar collections (`FoodConfig`, `ExerciseConfig`, …)

## Recalculation

Before persisting aggregates, recompute embedded `Calculation` on `DailyLog` from linked food/workout IDs (see TODOs in `domain/repo/*.dart`). Keep MET/burn logic in application or a dedicated `domain/calculation/` module — not in widgets.

## Generated code

After changing `@collection` / `@embedded` models:

```bash
cd flutter/weight_sovereignty && dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

Commit `*.g.dart` with the model change. Do not hand-edit generated files.

## Testing

- Unit-test services and calculation in `test/`
- Widget tests only for non-trivial presentation behavior
- Prefer faking repo interfaces over opening Isar in widget tests
